  "prompt": "Are there any sources or templates of stock Option agreement with employees?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several resources where you can find stock option agreement templates and examples for employees:\n\n1. Online Legal Platforms:\n- Google Legal Templates\n- LegalZoom\n- Rocket Lawyer\n- StartUpCounsel\n- NDA.com\n\n2. Startup/Venture Resources:\n- Y Combinator (SAFE and equity templates)\n- NVCA (National Venture Capital Association) documents\n- Series Seed Documents\n\n3. Professional Services:\n- Wilson Sonsini (free startup documents)\n- Cooley GO\n- Orrick Startup Forms\n\n4. Stock Option Agreement Specific Templates:\n- Carta (formerly eShares)\n- Pulley\n- Shareworks\n\n5. Free Resources:\n- GitHub repositories with startup legal templates\n- Open source startup legal document collections\n\nRecommended Best Practices:\n- Customize templates for your specific needs\n- Have a lawyer review the final document\n- Ensure compliance with local securities regulations\n- Clearly define vesting schedules, exercise prices, and conditions\n\nTips:\n- Consider consulting an employment lawyer\n- Use templates as starting points\n- Tailor documents to your specific company structure and goals\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these resources?",
